                     <layoutDesc>
                        <layout>
                           <p>Columns: 1;
                                                  ruled lines: 17;
                                                  written lines: 17; Uniform layout. Visible ruling with a mastara.Initial words of each section written in larger characters, preceded with a title page (see e.g. folio 224r, 240r, etc).Catchwords on every verso.The biblical verses are given with punctuation.</p>
                        </layout>
                     </layoutDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <scriptDesc>
                     <scriptNote>Square and semi-cursive Oriental script of the 17th century. Avraham ben Mordekhai ha-Kohen: inscribed, volume 2, folio 220v and volume 3, folio 126v. Avraham ha-Kohen wrote the present manuscript for his son, Yosef. The name of the latter is inscribed under the title of each Muḳadimah.</scriptNote>
                  </scriptDesc>
